<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1520,1820]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">
<taxonomicName authority="Ponza" authorityName="Ponza" authorityYear="1805" box="[151,474,1520,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Curculio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunonianus">
<emphasis box="[151,394,1520,1543]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">Curculio brunonianus</emphasis>
Ponza
</taxonomicName>
was listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sherborn, C. D." box="[660,838,1520,1543]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" pagination="641 - 943" refId="ref3259" refString="Sherborn, C. D. (1924) Index Animalium sive index nominum quae ab A. D. MDCCLFIII generibus et speciebus animalium imposita sunt. Societatibus eruditorum adiuvantibus a Carolo Davies Sherborn confectus. Sectio secunda a kalendis ianuariis, MDCCCI usque ad finem decembris, MDCCCL. Part IF. Index Bail. - Byzos. British Museum, London, pp. 641 - 943." type="book chapter" year="1924">Sherborn (1924</bibRefCitation>
: 916), neglected again in subsequent catalogues of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[151,305,1554,1577]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Curculionidae</taxonomicName>
, and considered a 
<emphasis box="[507,667,1554,1577]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">nomen dubium</emphasis>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Alonso-Zarazaga, M. A. &amp; Barrios, H. &amp; Borovec, R. &amp; Bouchard, P. &amp; Caldara, R. &amp; Colonnelli, E. &amp; Gultekin, L. &amp; Hlavac, P. &amp; Korotyaev, B. &amp; Lyal, C. H. C. &amp; Machado, A. &amp; Meregalli, M. &amp; Pierotti, H. &amp; Ren, L. &amp; Sanchez-Ruiz, M. &amp; Sforzi, A. &amp; Silfverberg, H. &amp; Skuhrovec, J. &amp; Tryzna, M. &amp; Velazquez De Castro, A. J. &amp; Yunakov, N. N." box="[710,1031,1554,1577]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" pagination="1 - 729" refId="ref1733" refString="Alonso-Zarazaga, M. A., Barrios, H., Borovec, R., Bouchard, P., Caldara, R., Colonnelli, E., Gultekin, L., Hlavac, P., Korotyaev, B., Lyal, C. H. C., Machado, A., Meregalli, M., Pierotti, H., Ren, L., Sanchez-Ruiz, M., Sforzi, A., Silfverberg, H., Skuhrovec, J., Tryzna, M., Velazquez De Castro, A. J. &amp; Yunakov, N. N. (2017) Cooperative catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera Curculionoidea. Monografias electronicas de la Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa, 8, 1 - 729. Available from: http: // sea-entomologia. org / monoelec. html (accessed 23 April 2019)" type="journal article" year="2017">
Alonso-Zarazaga 
<emphasis box="[902,950,1554,1577]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">et al</emphasis>
. (2017
</bibRefCitation>
: 538). Its 
<typeStatus box="[1142,1188,1554,1577]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">type</typeStatus>
was destroyed already before publication (
<bibRefCitation author="Ponza, L." box="[359,490,1589,1612]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" pagination="29 - 94" refId="ref3148" refString="Ponza, L. (1805) Coleoptera salutiensia sive enumeratio methodica coleopterorum, quae in agro salutiensi reperiuntur, locorum natalium indicatione, observationibus, novisque aliquot speciebus aucta. Memoires de l'Academie Imperiale des Sciences, Litterature et Beaux-Arts de Turin. Sciences Physiques et Mathematiques, 12 - 13 (1804 / 5), 29 - 94, pls. IV-V." type="journal article" year="1805">Ponza 1805</bibRefCitation>
: 39, footnote). 
<bibRefCitation author="Dutto, M. &amp; Poggi, R. &amp; Cavazzuti, P. F." box="[652,846,1589,1612]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" pagination="347 - 458" refId="ref2368" refString="Dutto, M., Poggi, R. &amp; Cavazzuti, P. F. (2009) I &quot; Coleoptera Salutiensia &quot; di Lorenzo Ponza (1805), con dati bio-bibliografici sull'autore e alcune note. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale &quot; G. Doria &quot;, 100, 347 - 458." type="journal article" year="2009">
Dutto 
<emphasis box="[719,765,1589,1612]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">et al</emphasis>
. (2009
</bibRefCitation>
: 428) pointed out that an anonymous hand-written note on a copy of 
<bibRefCitation author="Ponza, L." box="[310,476,1624,1647]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" pagination="29 - 94" refId="ref3148" refString="Ponza, L. (1805) Coleoptera salutiensia sive enumeratio methodica coleopterorum, quae in agro salutiensi reperiuntur, locorum natalium indicatione, observationibus, novisque aliquot speciebus aucta. Memoires de l'Academie Imperiale des Sciences, Litterature et Beaux-Arts de Turin. Sciences Physiques et Mathematiques, 12 - 13 (1804 / 5), 29 - 94, pls. IV-V." type="journal article" year="1805">Ponza’s (1805)</bibRefCitation>
paper refers this name to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Rossi, 1790)" authorityName="Rossi" authorityYear="1790" baseAuthorityName="Rossi" baseAuthorityYear="1790" box="[784,1120,1624,1647]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hylobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fatuus">
<emphasis box="[784,957,1624,1647]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">Hylobius fatuus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rossi, P." box="[977,1113,1624,1647]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" refId="ref3214" refString="Rossi, P. (1790) Fauna etrusca sistens insecta quae in provinciis florentina et pisana praesertim collegit Petrus Rossius in Regio Pisano Athenaeo. Tomus primus. Typis Thomae Masi, Sociorum, Liburni, XXII + 272 pp., 1 pl" type="book" year="1790">Rossi, 1790</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, which is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Goeze, 1777) (Alonso-Zarazaga et al. 2017)" authorityName="Alonso-Zarazaga et al." authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Goeze" baseAuthorityYear="1777" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hylobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transversovittatus">
<emphasis box="[1410,1429,1624,1647]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,342,1658,1681]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">transversovittatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Goeze, J. A. E." box="[359,500,1658,1681]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" refId="ref2613" refString="Goeze, J. A. E. (1777) Entomologische Beytrage zu des Ritter Linne zwolften Ausgabe des Natursystems. Erster Teil. Weidmanns Erben und Reich, Leipzig, XVI + 736 pp." type="book" year="1777">Goeze, 1777</bibRefCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Alonso-Zarazaga, M. A. &amp; Barrios, H. &amp; Borovec, R. &amp; Bouchard, P. &amp; Caldara, R. &amp; Colonnelli, E. &amp; Gultekin, L. &amp; Hlavac, P. &amp; Korotyaev, B. &amp; Lyal, C. H. C. &amp; Machado, A. &amp; Meregalli, M. &amp; Pierotti, H. &amp; Ren, L. &amp; Sanchez-Ruiz, M. &amp; Sforzi, A. &amp; Silfverberg, H. &amp; Skuhrovec, J. &amp; Tryzna, M. &amp; Velazquez De Castro, A. J. &amp; Yunakov, N. N." box="[525,845,1658,1681]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" pagination="1 - 729" refId="ref1733" refString="Alonso-Zarazaga, M. A., Barrios, H., Borovec, R., Bouchard, P., Caldara, R., Colonnelli, E., Gultekin, L., Hlavac, P., Korotyaev, B., Lyal, C. H. C., Machado, A., Meregalli, M., Pierotti, H., Ren, L., Sanchez-Ruiz, M., Sforzi, A., Silfverberg, H., Skuhrovec, J., Tryzna, M., Velazquez De Castro, A. J. &amp; Yunakov, N. N. (2017) Cooperative catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera Curculionoidea. Monografias electronicas de la Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa, 8, 1 - 729. Available from: http: // sea-entomologia. org / monoelec. html (accessed 23 April 2019)" type="journal article" year="2017">
Alonso-Zarazaga 
<emphasis box="[721,770,1658,1681]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. From this and the original description, we formally synonymize 
<taxonomicName authority="Ponza, 1805" authorityName="Ponza" authorityYear="1805" box="[286,590,1693,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Curculio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunonianus">
<emphasis box="[286,451,1693,1716]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">C. brunonianus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ponza, L." box="[459,590,1693,1716]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" pagination="29 - 94" refId="ref3148" refString="Ponza, L. (1805) Coleoptera salutiensia sive enumeratio methodica coleopterorum, quae in agro salutiensi reperiuntur, locorum natalium indicatione, observationibus, novisque aliquot speciebus aucta. Memoires de l'Academie Imperiale des Sciences, Litterature et Beaux-Arts de Turin. Sciences Physiques et Mathematiques, 12 - 13 (1804 / 5), 29 - 94, pls. IV-V." type="journal article" year="1805">Ponza, 1805</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Goeze, 1777)" authorityName="Alonso-Zarazaga et al." authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Goeze" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[651,1146,1693,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hylobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transversovittatus" subGenus="Callirus">
<emphasis box="[651,678,1693,1716]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">H.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[693,780,1693,1716]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">Callirus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[796,987,1693,1716]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">transversovittatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Goeze, J. A. E." box="[1001,1138,1693,1716]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" refId="ref2613" refString="Goeze, J. A. E. (1777) Entomologische Beytrage zu des Ritter Linne zwolften Ausgabe des Natursystems. Erster Teil. Weidmanns Erben und Reich, Leipzig, XVI + 736 pp." type="book" year="1777">Goeze, 1777</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1161,1330,1693,1716]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">new synonymy</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1520,1820]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">
In 
<collectingCountry box="[228,278,1728,1751]" name="Italy" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">Italy</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alonso-Zarazaga et al." authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Goeze" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[289,514,1728,1751]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hylobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transversovittatus">
<emphasis box="[289,514,1728,1751]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">H. transversovittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs across most of the mainland regions and in 
<collectingRegion box="[1067,1129,1728,1751]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">Sicily</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Abbazzi, P. &amp; Maggini, L." box="[1143,1425,1728,1751]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" pagination="29 - 216" refId="ref1642" refString="Abbazzi, P. &amp; Maggini, L. (2009) Elenco sistematico-faunistico dei Curculionoidea italiani, Scolytidae e Platypodidae esclusi (Insecta, Coleoptera). Aldrovandia, 5, 29 - 216." type="journal article" year="2009">Abbazzi &amp; Maggini 2009</bibRefCitation>
). In this country, from a conservation point of view, the species is classified as “Least Concern” (
<bibRefCitation author="Colonnelli, E. &amp; Gatti, E." box="[1165,1428,1762,1785]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197" pagination="77 - 80" refId="ref2091" refString="Colonnelli, E. &amp; Gatti, E. (2015) Family Curculionidae. In: Carpaneto, G. M., Baviera, C., Biscaccianti, A. B., Brandmayr, P., Mazzei, A., Mason, F., Battistoni, A., Teofli, C., Rondinini, C., Fattorini, S. &amp; Audisio, P. (Eds.), A Red List of Italian Saproxylic Beetles: taxonomic overview, ecological features and conservation issues (Coleoptera). Fragmenta Entomologica, 47 (2), pp. 77 - 80." type="journal article" year="2015">Colonnelli &amp; Gatti 2015</bibRefCitation>
) but, in reality, is it becoming very rare and even disappearing from many localities (E. Colonnelli, unpublished data).
</paragraph>
